JWT(json web Token) for authenticatioon 
token and bcrypt is used
if all routes are in same file it gets cluter
user and  upload routes and kept separate
router => used to create routes
no routes are made in app.js they just config the router
express validator => checks the data if its write or wrong.
we dont write the url directly we make it a enviornmental variable
in the .env file (all the secrets are in there)
password is not saved normaly it is saved in hash form
bcrypt is used to convert password to hash
token is generated because a user only logins once and then further he remains autherized.
multer to get file fron frontend to storage.